{
  "stem": "71.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And apparently my father and my uncle were the only ones in Poland to have a-- as Jews, have a business like that.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Most of this business was given to military people that were awarded because of the-- of-- of war achievements.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it's-- in 1933, when the government in Poland changed, this business was taken away from my father, because he was a Jew.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my father almost lost his livelihood because there was a large family to support, and there were no means to support.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But somehow my sisters were already older, and some of them went to work.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we sustained ourselves.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Never ?] [? a ?] [? nice ?] [? man. ?] So it became very difficult, because there was not an income as we were-- my parents were used to.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But somehow we sustained ourselves.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I went to a private school all my life, all my schooled life.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was a Jewish-- a girls Jewish school, Bais Yaakov, and it was quite expensive.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Not every person in Lodz could afford.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But as I said, my husband-- my father was in business and he could afford, and he emphasized on education.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Although they believed that-- those years, that only boys should have education.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He was intelligent enough to understand that-- that girls as well need education as the same as boys.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Therefore, he sent us to private schools and--",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All the children are-- were educated.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had a sister, the second of the old-- from the oldest, who was one of the most gifted accountants in this city.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She-- she kept a very high position.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
